<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,353,560]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,171,354,380]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,257,360,377]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">REMARKS</emphasis>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[257,264,354,380]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">.</emphasis>
The genus was recently resurrected for the southern group of species previously assigned to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sta" authorityName="Sta" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Odopoea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1334,1437,353,379]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Odopoea</emphasis>
Stå
</taxonomicName>
1, 1861 (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[289,469,389,416]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 104" refId="ref108562" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2019 b) The cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Bolivia including the descriptions of fifteen new species, the resurrection of one genus and two species, seven new combinations, six new synonymies, and twenty-eight new records. Zootaxa, 4655 (1), 1 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4655.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">Sanborn 2019b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deletang" authorityYear="1919" box="[488,647,389,415]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Edholmbergia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[488,647,389,415]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Edholmbergia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was synonymized at the same time (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[1072,1251,389,416]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 104" refId="ref108562" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2019 b) The cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Bolivia including the descriptions of fifteen new species, the resurrection of one genus and two species, seven new combinations, six new synonymies, and twenty-eight new records. Zootaxa, 4655 (1), 1 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4655.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">Sanborn 2019b</bibRefCitation>
). The species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Haupt, 1918" authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1918" box="[151,249,425,451]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Adusella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,249,425,451]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Adusella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the other Peruvian cicada taxa by the lateral extensions of the pronotum and the three tarsomeres (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." box="[350,527,461,488]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 104" refId="ref108562" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2019 b) The cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Bolivia including the descriptions of fifteen new species, the resurrection of one genus and two species, seven new combinations, six new synonymies, and twenty-eight new records. Zootaxa, 4655 (1), 1 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4655.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">Sanborn 2019b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
